{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἐπίστᾰμαι</b>, 2 <br /> <i>person</i> <b>-ασαι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 376, 982, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 629, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 296a, but ἐπίστᾳ 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 3.80, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 86, 581, ἐπίστῃ 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 1085, “PCair.Zen.” 41.19 (3rd c.BC), _Ionic dialect_ ἐπίστεαι ἐξ-) 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.135; _imperative_ ἐπίστασο [prev. work] 29, 209, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 840, 967, “PCair.Zen.” 57.4 (3rd c.BC), etc., but ἐπίσταο variant in 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.209 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], <i>contraction</i> ἐπίστω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 658, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>subjunctive</i> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἐπιστέωμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.134 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Attic dialect</i> ἐπίστωμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Euthydemus” 296a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>imperfect</i> ἠπιστάμην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 267, etc.; without augment ἐπίστατο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.60: 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus has ἐπ- 5.42 (variant ἠπ-), ἠπ- 3.139 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Ionic dialect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> ἠπιστέατο or ἐπιστέατο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8.132 \">Refs</a>]: <i>future</i> ἐπιστήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.320, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist 1</i> ἠπιστήθην [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.15, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 687a. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__I</b></Level2>. <b>know</b> how to do, <b>be able</b> to do, <b>capable</b> of doing, c.<i>infinitive</i>, οὐδέ οἱ ὀστέ᾽ ἐπιστήσονται Ἀχαιοὶ ἀλλέξαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 21.320, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.207, 7th-6th c.BC: Sappho Lyrica 70, etc.: 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus has it both of intellectual power, ὅς τις ἐπίσταιτο ᾗσι φρεσὶν ἄρτια βάζειν 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.92; ἐπιστάμεναι σάφα θυμῷ 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.730 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; and of artistic skill, ὃς χερσὶν ἐπίστατο δαίδαλα πάντα τεύχειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 5.60 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: frequently in Trag. and <i>Attic dialect</i>, οὔπω σωφρονεῖν ἐπίστασαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 982, compare 1032, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 589; πένεσθαι δ᾽ οὐκ ἐ. δόμος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 962; ἐ... θεοὺς σέβειν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 996, cf. Alcaeus566 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κιθαρίζειν οὐκ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 989, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 223d, “R.” 420e, +others: without \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, σῷζ ὅπως ἐπίστασαι as best you <b>can</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 376, compare “Eu.” 581. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__I.2</b></Level3>. <b>to be assured, feel sure</b> that.., τοῦτον ἐπίστανται πλεῖστα εἰδέναι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 57, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.134, 139, 6.139, +others: followed by ὡς, [prev. author] 1.122. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2>. with <i>accusative</i>, <b>understand</b> a matter, <b>know, be versed in</b> or <b>acquainted with</b>, πολλὰ δ᾽ ἐπίστατο ἔργα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 23.705, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.117; Μουσέων δῶρον 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 1; τὴν τέχνην 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.130; τὸ μέλλον 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 373; ἐμπειρίᾳ ἐ. τὴν ναυτικήν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.10; τὰς φύσεις ὑμῶν [prev. author] 7.14; πάσας τὰς δημιουργίας 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 598c \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἔγωγε γράμματ᾽ οὐδ᾽ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 122 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ μὴ ἐ. γράμματα illiteracy, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PRyl.” 73.19 (1st c.BC), etc.\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ἱερατικὰ καὶ Αἰγύπτια γράμματα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PTeb.” 291.41 (2nd c.AD)\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἐ. μύθους τοὺς Αἰσώπου <b>know</b> them <b>by heart</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 61b, compare “Grg.” 484b: also with an \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] <i>adverb</i>, Συριστὶ ἐ. <b>know</b> Syrian, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.5.31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; with <i>accusative</i> and <i>infinitive</i> conjoined, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 276 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; with <i>infinitive</i> to explanation the <i>accusative</i>, ἔργον δὲ μοῦνον ἐσθίειν ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC(?): Semonides Iambographus 7.24, compare 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 65. \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3>. after [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], <b>know</b> as a fact, <b>know</b> <b>for certain</b>, ἐπισταμένοισι εὖ οὐκ ἄν τις λέγοι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.8.ά, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; used convertibly with εἰδέναι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 163b, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Analytica Priora” 66b31, “Ph.” 184a10 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; even χάριν ἐ., ={χάριν εἰδέναι}, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 8.246c (but sometimes εἰδέναι is general, ἐπίστασθαι\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>] being confined to <b>scientific knowledge</b> (ἐπιστήμη), διὰ τὸ εἰδέναι τὸ ἐπίστασθαι ἐδίωκον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Metaphysica” 982b21): frequently strengthened, εὖ ἐ\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]. Hdt.[same place]; σαφῶς ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 840, etc.: most frequently with _accusative_, τὰ διαφέροντα ἐ. 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 4.19, etc.; also ἐ. περί τινος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.3, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.60; περὶ θεῶν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 795.4: followed by a dependent clause, τί σφιν χρήσηται ἐ. 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 772 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ἐ. ὅτι.., or ἐ. τοῦτο, ὅτι.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.3, 156, etc.; ὡς.. 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 599; τοῦτ᾽ ἐπίστασ᾽, ὡς 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1370; ἐ. αὐτὸν οἷς ψωμίζεται 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 715, etc. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3>. rarely, <b>know</b> a person, Ἀρίγνωτον γὰρ οὐδεὶς ὅστις οὐκ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1278, compare 1st c.AD: Musonius Philosophus “fragment” 3p.12H., 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Asin.” 1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸν Ἰησοῦν γινώσκω καὶ τὸν Παῦλον ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.Act.19.15 \">NT</a>]; but ὁ παῖς τοὺς τεκόντας οὐκ ἐ. <b>does</b> not <b>know who</b> they <b>are</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 51. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2>. with <i>participle</i>, in Prose and Trag., <b>know that</b> one is, has, etc., εὖ ἐ. αὐτὸς σχήσων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.42; ἐσθλὸς ὢν ἐπίστασο 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1399, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also ὡς ὧδ᾽ ἐχόντων τῶνδ᾽ ἐ. σε χρή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 281 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὡς φανέν γε τοὔπος ὧδ᾽ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “OT” 848: with double _accusative_, ἑαυτοὺς Φαυστύλου ἠπιστάμεθα παῖδας (i.e. ὄντας) 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Romulus” 7 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: c.<i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1092, 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator “Fragmenta” 53.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2>. <i>present</i> <i>participle</i> ἐπιστάμενος, η, ον, frequently as <i>adjective</i>, <b>knowing, understanding, skilful</b>, ἀνδρὸς ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.359; χαλεπὸν ἐ. περ ἐόντι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 19.80 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; καὶ μάλ᾽ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 13.313 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; even of a dancer's feet, θρέξασκον ἐπισταμένοισι πόδεσσι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.599: also with _genitive_, φόρμιγγος ἐ. καὶ ἀοιδῆς\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] <b>skilled, versed in</b> them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 21.406: and with _dative_, ἄκοντι 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.282: hence, \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__IV.2</b></Level3>. <i>adverb</i> ἐπιστᾰμένως <b>skilfully, expertly</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7.317, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 87, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; εὖ καὶ ἐ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.265, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 20.161, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 107; ἐ. πίνειν 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 212 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also in Prose, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.1.3, 2nd c.AD: Apollonius Dyscolus Grammaticus “de Adverbiis;” 146.7, Vett. Val. 298.2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: c.<i>infinitive</i>, <b>with knowledge</b> how to.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “De rerum natura - Wien. Stud.” 14.4. (Since ἐφίστημι τὸν νοῦν is used in the sense of ἐπίσταμαι\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>], <b>attend, observe</b>, it is probably that ἐπίσταμαι is merely an old <i>middle</i> form of ἐφίστημι,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Physica” 247b11 τῷ γὰρ ἠρεμῆσαι καὶ στῆναι τὴν διάνοιαν ἐπίστασθαι.. λέγομεν, and see at {ἐπίστασις} II.2.) \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G1987","accentedUnicode":"ἐπίσταμαι","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G1990","matchingForm":"ἐπιστήμων","stepTransliteration":"epistēmōn","gloss":"knowing","_zh_tw_Gloss":"有見識","_es_Gloss":"entendido","_zh_Gloss":"有见识"},{"strongNumber":"G2186","matchingForm":"ἐφίστημι","stepTransliteration":"efistēmi","gloss":"to approach","_zh_tw_Gloss":"站在, 進前來","_es_Gloss":"acercarse","_zh_Gloss":"站在, 进前来"}],"shortDef":"to understand, know, be aware","mediumDef":"to understand, know, be aware <br /><b>to be versed in, to be master of,</b> <ref='1Ti.6.4'>1Tim. 6:4;</ref> <b>to be acquainted with,</b> <ref='Act.18.25'>Acts 18:25;</ref> 19:15; Jude 10: <b>to know,</b> <ref='Act.10.28'>Acts 10:28;</ref> <b>to remember, comprehend, understand,</b> <ref='Mrk.14.68'>Mk. 14:68</ref>","stepGloss":"to know/understand","stepTransliteration":"epistamai","count":14,"_es_Definition":"saber, entender","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 明白 (可 14:68; 提前 6:4)<br>2) 知道, 熟知<br>5","_zh_Definition":"1) 明白 (可 14:68; 提前 6:4)<br>2) 知道, 熟知<br>5","_step_Type":"verb","_vi_Definition":"nhận ra; hiểu; biết","_zh_tw_Gloss":"知道","_es_Gloss":"saber/entender","_zh_Gloss":"知道"}]}